    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start, very atmospheric. to make it even more realistic for the script, i want to ground it in the people who inhabit the area. can you describe some of the groups or types of people you'd see hanging out on these corners or in these alleys? i want to show the different vibes—like the people who live there vs the people who might be coming in looking for trouble. just give me some character archetypes to help the actors.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You'll see the \"locals\"—a mix of drugged-out veterans and recent immigrants who huddle in hazy clusters, their faces etched with a permanent, weary resignation that masks deep-seated resentment. Contrast them with the \"visitors,\" a group of disheveled, aggressive men who loiter with predatory glances, often wearing cheap suits that scream desperation and looking for easy targets or a fight. There are also the silent watchers, elderly residents who stare out from their broken-down apartments with hollow eyes, knowing that the only thing keeping the neighborhood from total collapse is the very fear they all share. These archetypes should feel like a fragile ecosystem where every glance could ignite a conflict, and no one is truly safe.",
